ion Marker","value":"A behind-the-scenes marker that keeps your sign-in tied together while you enter your code. You never see or handle it."},{"label":"Code Box","value":"Where you type your six-digit code. It must match the current code from your device."},{"label":"Remember This Device","value":"Check this to skip the code step next time on this computer."},{"label":"Use Recovery Code","value":"Switches to entering a backup code instead, in case you can't reach your app."},{"label":"Hidden Contact Info","value":"For codes sent by text or email, shows a partly hidden phone number or email, such as '***-***-1234' or 'j***@example.com.' Not used for authenticator apps."}]},{"heading":"Rules for Each Field","items":[{"label":"Verification Code","value":"Required. Must be exactly six digits and match the current code from your app. A wrong code shows an error below the box."},{"label":"Recovery Code","value":"Required. Must match one of your unused backup codes. Each code works only once and can't be reused."},{"label":"Removing a Device","value":"Asks you to confirm first. Warns that removing your only device could lock you out."},{"label":"Turning Off Two-Step Sign-In","value":"Asks you to confirm first. Removes all your devices and recovery codes. You can't turn it off if your admin requires it for your role."},{"label":"Saving Admin Rules","value":"You can pick any number of roles, or none at all (none means no rule). Changes take effect as soon as you save."}]},{"heading":"Ways to Get Your Code","items":[{"label":"Authenticator App","value":"The main, recommended way. Apps like Google Authenticator or Authy show a six-digit code that changes every 30 seconds."},{"label":"Security Key","value":"A hardware key (such as a YubiKey) or built-in option like Windows Hello or Touch ID. You tap or plug it in instead of typing a code."},{"label":"Text Message","value":"A code sent by text to your phone. Less safe than an app, since phone numbers can be hijacked."},{"label":"Email","value":"A code sent to your email. A backup for when nothing else is available."}]},{"heading":"About Your Devices","items":[{"label":"Device Kind","value":"How this device gives you codes — authenticator app, text, email, or security key."},{"label":"Your Secret Key","value":"The private key that lets your app make matching codes. It's kept scrambled and is never shown again after setup."},{"label":"Device Name","value":"The name you chose, such as 'My iPhone.' If you didn't set one, the device kind is shown instead."},{"label":"Confirmed","value":"Shows that you finished setup by entering a code. Unconfirmed devices can't be used to sign in."},{"label":"Default","value":"Marks your main device — the one asked for first when you sign in. Only one device is the default."},{"label":"Last Used","value":"When you last signed in with this device, shown as MM/dd/yyyy. Blank if never used."},{"label":"Failed Tries","value":"Counts wrong codes in a row. Too many in a row locks the device for a while."},{"label":"Locked Until","value":"If too many wrong codes lock the device, this is when it unlocks. Blank when it's not locked."}]},{"heading":"About Your Recovery Codes","items":[{"label":"Stored Safely","value":"Your recovery codes are kept scrambled. The real codes are shown only once when created and never stored, so save them right away."},{"label":"Used","value":"Marks a code as spent after you use it to sign in. Used codes can't be reused."},{"label":"Used On","value":"The date and time a code was used. Blank if it hasn't been used."},{"label":"Used From","value":"The location a code was used from, kept for security review."}]}]}"""
